Text: The first week back at University for the semester is exciting, especially after being away for so much of last semester.
Going into our second studio project I have become more aware of my skill set and what kind of project I would like to work on.
This has been learnt from our previous studio project where I felt unable to contribute due to massive gaps in technical knowledge regarding database design, building a dashboard and using R studio.
From the feedback received I am now more in touch with how I work and contribute to the team.
I am looking forward to this project due to it being the beginnings of a system which will help our client, Kevin, automate data collection through web scraping.
The end goal is to build a system which he can automatically collect data, analyse it, and make predictions on the likelihood greyhounds will win in races.
Although this project is just for personal use, it provides clear objectives and an obvious direction.

I feel more confident in this project as we are building something from scratch which means we avoid the difficulties of integrating the solution we are working with into an existing system or database.

This was a huge struggle in the previous project as the clients seemed to lack purpose and intention with the layout of their web application and structure of their database which made the project complicated alongside the ever changing client expectations and understanding the benefits of impacted stakeholder groups.

Starting a project from scratch is a new and unique experience and I imagine it does not resemble working in the tech field, although it is exciting and a great opportunity to learn as we have a metaphorical clean slate.
